# Banking App

This is a simple banking application that allows users to deposit, withdraw, and check their balance.

## Prerequisites

- Node.js installed on your machine
- MongoDB installed and running locally

## Installation

1. Clone the repository to your local machine:

https://github.com/leon-bi/Bank.git

2. Navigate to the project directory:

3. Install dependencies using npm:

4. Start the server:

This will start the Express server at `http://localhost:3000`.

5. Open your web browser and go to `http://localhost:3000` to access the application.

Also use Postman to see the actual logic if its not working

http://localhost:3000/deposit
http://localhost:3000/withdraw
http://localhost:3000/balance

## Usage

1. Deposit Money:
- Enter the amount you want to deposit in the "Deposit Amount" field.
- Click the "Deposit" button.
- The deposited amount will be added to your balance.

2. Withdraw Money:
- Enter the amount you want to withdraw in the "Withdraw Amount" field.
- Click the "Withdraw" button.
- The specified amount will be deducted from your balance.

3. Check Balance:
- Click the "Check Balance" button.
- Your current balance will be displayed.

